 other in <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2009/jul/04/one-day-david-nicholls-review\">One Day</a>, also including other tracks he imagined his character Emma would like. There’s also Stephen King’s Doctor Sleep playlist, or (of course) Nick Hornby’s one for his novel High Fidelity:</p>  <figure class=\"element element-embed\" data-alt=\"high fidelity playlist\">  <iframe src=\"https://embed.spotify.com/?uri=spotify:user:kakaoo:playlist:1igRIFXPyiLTL1Dyipus7k\" frameborder=\"0\" allowtransparency=\"true\" width=\"300\" height=\"380\"></iframe> </figure>  <p>We also adore projects elsewhere on the internet like Maria Popova’s <a href=\"http://literaryjukebox.brainpickings.org/page/3\">Literary jukebox</a>, where she matches great quotes from literature with songs.</p> <p><strong>We now would love to hear what background music you prefer to read to, and what specific music-literature pairings you find perfect. Be as specific or as general as you like. We will feature a selection on playlists on the Guardian site.</strong></p>  <figure class=\"element element-embed\" data-alt=\"books-music pairings\">  <iframe class=\"fenced\" srcdoc=\"&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;https://guardiannewsampampmedia.formstack.com/forms/js.php/booksmusic_pairings&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;noscript&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://guardiannewsampampmedia.formstack.com/forms/untitled_form_179&quot; title=&quot;Online Form&quot;&gt;Online Form - Untitled Form&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/noscript&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align:right; font-size:x-small;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.formstack.com?utm_source=jsembed&amp;utm_medium=product&amp;utm_campaign=product+branding&amp;fa=h,2221988&quot; title=&quot;HTML Form Creator&quot;&gt;HTML Form Creator&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;\"></iframe> </figure>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4fgjf","wordcount":"219","thumbnail":"http://med